.TH JFC 1 "2026-04-11" "jfc" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jfc \- format JSON files with configurable, Prettier-style ergonomics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jfc
[\fB--write\fR | \fB--check\fR | \fB--list-different\fR]
[\fB--config\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--stdin-filepath\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fIFILE\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jfc
formats JSON files and stdin using a small, predictable formatter with TOML-based project configuration.
It is intentionally shaped like a JSON-only Prettier-style CLI, including support for
\fB--write\fR,
\fB--check\fR,
and
\fB--list-different\fR.
.PP
When no file arguments are provided, or when a lone
\fB-\fR
is passed, input is read from standard input.
Directories are traversed recursively and shell globs may be passed through the invoking shell.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --write
Format matching files in place.
This option cannot be used with stdin.
.TP
.B --check
Print files whose formatted output differs from the current contents and exit with status 1 when any differ.
.TP
.B --list-different
Print files whose formatted output differs from the current contents and exit with status 1 when any differ.
.TP
.B --config PATH
Load configuration from the specified
\fBjfc.toml\fR
file instead of walking upward from the target file or stdin path.
.TP
.B --stdin-filepath PATH
Resolve stdin configuration as if the input originated from
\fIPATH\fR.
This is useful when piping content from editors or other tools while still wanting project-local config discovery.
.TP
.B --help
Show usage information.
.SH CONFIGURATION
By default,
.B jfc
looks for
\fBjfc.toml\fR
starting from the file being formatted and walking upward toward the filesystem root.
If stdin is used, discovery starts from the current working directory unless
\fB--stdin-filepath\fR
is provided.
.PP
Supported top-level keys:
.TP
.B use_tabs
Use hard tabs for indentation.
.TP
.B tab_width
Visual width for one indent level.
.TP
.B print_width
Target width used to decide whether arrays and objects should remain inline when expansion is set to
\fBauto\fR.
.TP
.B trailing_newline
Append a final newline when true.
.TP
.B sort_keys
Sort object keys lexicographically when true.
.TP
.B array_expand
One of
\fBauto\fR,
\fBalways\fR,
or
\fBnever\fR.
.TP
.B object_expand
One of
\fBauto\fR,
\fBalways\fR,
or
\fBnever\fR.
.TP
.B space_after_colon
Render object members as
\fB"key": value\fR
instead of
\fB"key":value\fR.
.TP
.B space_within_braces
Add spaces just inside
\fB{\fR
and
\fB}\fR
for inline objects.
.TP
.B space_within_brackets
Add spaces just inside
\fB[\fR
and
\fB]\fR
for inline arrays.
.TP
.B end_of_line
One of
\fBlf\fR,
\fBcrlf\fR,
or
\fBcr\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Formatting differences were found during
\fB--check\fR
or
\fB--list-different\fR.
.TP
.B 2
Parse, configuration, IO, or usage error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Format a file to stdout:
.B jfc package.json
.TP
Format stdin:
.B cat package.json | jfc
.TP
Rewrite files in place:
.B jfc --write .
.TP
Check formatting in CI:
.B jfc --check .
.TP
Use an explicit config:
.B jfc --config ./config/jfc.toml data/example.json
.TP
Use stdin with project config discovery:
.B cat data.json | jfc --stdin-filepath apps/api/data.json
.SH FILES
.TP
.B jfc.toml
Project-local formatter configuration.
.SH COOKBOOK
.TP
Use hard tabs:
.RS
.nf
use_tabs = true
tab_width = 4
.fi
.RE
.TP
Sort generated JSON deterministically:
.RS
.nf
sort_keys = true
object_expand = "always"
array_expand = "always"
.fi
.RE
.TP
Normalize line endings for cross-platform repositories:
.RS
.nf
end_of_line = "lf"
trailing_newline = true
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR jq (1)
